article.headline: Marist 77, Manhattan 68
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. (AP) -- Ryan Stilphen scored 21 points and had 11 rebounds to lead Marist to a 77-68 win over Manhattan in Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference play Wednesday. It was Manhattan's first conference loss. The visitors managed to lead briefly by two points early on, while Marist held as much as a 13-point lead. Marist (9-6, 3-4 MAAC) also got 13 points from James Smith and 10 from Will Whittington. Arturo Dubois scored 26 and had 12 rebounds to lead Manhattan (10-5, 6-1) before fouling out. Jason Wingate added 16 points and Jeff Xavier had 12. Marist led 40-34 at the half. Manhattan shot just 39 percent for the game.
